news.title: CCI okays Dalmia Bharat's proposal to acquire Jaiprakash Associates
news.para: The Competition Commission of India (CCI) has approved Dalmia Bharat's resolution plan to acquire the debt-laden Jaiprakash Associates Ltd (JAL) through the insolvency resolution process. Several other entities, including Adani Enterprises and Vedanta Group, have also sought CCI approval to submit their resolution plans. JAL, undergoing CIRP after defaulting on loans, has significant real estate and cement assets.

news.title: Knowledge Realty Trust REIT IPO fully subscribed on day 1
news.para: Knowledge Realty Trust's Rs 4,800-crore IPO saw full subscription on day one. The IPO received bids for 25,04,91,300 units. Institutional investors showed strong interest. The company already raised Rs 1,620 crore from anchor investors. Knowledge Realty Trust aims to become India's largest REIT. The IPO will conclude on August 7. The company owns significant office assets across major cities.

news.title: Prestige Estates Projects' net profit rises 1.47% in Q1 FY26
news.para: Prestige Estates Projects announced a marginal increase in net consolidated profit, reaching ₹311.50 crore in Q1 FY26, up from ₹307 crore year-over-year. The company's total income also saw substantial growth, rising by 21.94% to ₹2,468.70 crore.

news.title: Minister distributes land documents to 120 families in Ernakulam
news.para: Local Self-Government Minister M B Rajesh emphasized the importance of projects fulfilling families' life dreams at a land document distribution event for 120 landless families, part of Ernakulam district panchayat's LIFE project. He lauded the panchayat's land purchase initiative and announced a record allocation of 100,000 homes this year under the LIFE housing project, a model scheme nationwide.

news.title: Tesla leases 33,000 sq ft commercial space in Gurugram
news.para: Tesla has leased a 33,000 sq ft space in Gurugram's Orchid Business Park for nine years, intended as a service, delivery, and retail center. The lease, registered on July 28, commences immediately with a starting rent of Rs 40 lakh, escalating annually by 4.75%.

news.title: Simon Property Group reports rise in quarterly real estate FFO on strong leasing demand
news.para: Simon Property Group reported a rise in second-quarter real estate funds from operations (FFO), driven by strong leasing demand and a tight supply of rental properties. Occupancy levels increased to 96%, with base minimum rent per square foot rising to $58.70. The company now expects its 2025 FFO to be between $12.45 and $12.65 per share.

news.title: Ummeed Housing secures ₹250 crore from BII to boost affordable housing
news.para: Ummeed Housing Finance has secured Rs 250 crore in funding from British International Investment to provide affordable housing finance to low-income groups in India. These mortgage-backed loans will empower underserved borrowers, particularly women, through property ownership and financial inclusion.

news.title: SC cancels bail granted to DHFL promoter in loan scam case, directs him to surrender in two weeks
news.para: The Supreme Court overturned Dheeraj Wadhawan's bail in a multi-crore bank loan scam. A medical board report prompted the decision. The Delhi High Court had granted bail on medical grounds. The CBI challenged this, arguing Wadhawan wasn't seriously ill and siphoned off funds. Dheeraj and Kapil Wadhawan were arrested in July 2022.

news.title: Sumadhura Capitol Towers lease out five lakh sq ft space in Bengaluru
news.para: Sumadhura Group has leased five lakh sq ft at Sumadhura Capitol Towers in Bengaluru. Global businesses will use the space for office and retail. The leasing is expected to generate ₹50 crore annually. Sumadhura Capitol Towers, designed by Morphogenesis, spans 8.67 acres. It has a leasable area of 1.5 million sq ft.

news.title: Assetz acquires 11.5 acres land in East Bengaluru
news.para: Assetz, a Bengaluru-based company, has acquired 11.5 acres of land on Old Madras Road. They plan to build a luxury residential community. The project's estimated value exceeds ₹1,400 crore. Motilal Oswal Alternates supports this acquisition. The development will include approximately 800 units. Assetz has secured a pipeline of 17 million square feet across 19 projects.

news.title: Orient Bell posts net loss of 37.48 lakh in Q1 FY26
news.para: Orient Bell reported a net consolidated loss after tax of ₹37.48 lakh for the quarter ended June 30, 2025, a notable improvement from the ₹1.86 crore loss in the same period last year. The company's net consolidated total income experienced a slight decrease of 3.41%, reaching ₹143.61 crore in Q1 FY26.

news.title: Ashiana Housing plans ₹425 crore outlay for FY26
news.para: Ashiana Housing will invest ₹425 crore in senior living during FY26, expanding into Mumbai, Bengaluru, and Delhi-NCR. This follows a ₹213 crore outlay in FY25, which saw ₹382 crore in bookings. The company plans to launch five new phases in existing projects, totaling 5.71 lakh sq ft.

news.title: Raymond Realty posts standalone profit of ₹26.93 crore in Q1 FY26
news.para: Raymond Realty, the real estate arm of Raymond Group, announced a standalone profit after tax of ₹26.93 crore for Q1 FY26. The company's total income stood at ₹334.34 crore. Bookings reached ₹306 crore, with collections at ₹374 crore. Raymond Realty is net-debt free with a cash surplus. The company plans expansion through joint development agreements.

news.title: Keystone Realtors' net profit declines 36.34% in Q1 FY26
news.para: Keystone Realtors experienced a decrease in net profit during the first quarter of fiscal year 2026. The company's profit after tax was approximately sixteen crore rupees. However, pre-sales showed significant growth, reaching over one thousand crore rupees. Three new projects were launched in Q1 FY26. Boman Irani highlighted the success of their business model.

news.title: Berger Paints' net profit dips 11% in Q1 FY26
news.para: Berger Paints experienced a decrease in net consolidated profit for the quarter ending June 30, 2025. Profit after tax was Rupees 315.04 crore. This is against Rupees 354.03 crore in the previous fiscal year. Total income saw a slight increase. A fire at a Kolkata warehouse caused an exceptional loss. The company is filing an insurance claim.

news.title: About 50% of Bhandara located on nazul land, govt to regularize these properties: Revenue minister
news.para: Revenue Minister Chandrashekhar Bawankule announced plans to regularize nazul land in Bhandara city within a year using drone surveys, addressing the lack of ownership rights for nearly 50% of residents. A re-survey of sand resources will also be conducted to accurately assess availability, followed by auctions.

news.title: Civic bodies demolish nine 'unsafe' buildings in Jaipur
news.para: Jaipur authorities took action against unsafe buildings. Nine structures were demolished by Jaipur Municipal Corporation-Heritage and Greater. The demolitions occurred in areas like Tripolia Bazaar and Mansarovar. Notices were issued to owners of dilapidated buildings. The move aims to prevent monsoon-related accidents. Authorities are prioritizing public safety by removing hazardous structures. More demolitions are expected.

news.title: Vascon Engineers posts net profit of ₹22.47 crore in Q1 FY26
news.para: Vascon Engineers announced a substantial increase in net consolidated profit for the quarter ending June 30, 2025. The company's profit after tax reached ₹22.47 crore. There is a notable rise from ₹9.60 crore in the previous fiscal year. Net consolidated total income also grew to ₹241.96 crore. Santosh Sundararajan's reappointment as whole time director got approval.

news.title: New Chandigarh farmers still await plots under 2013 pooling scheme
news.para: Farmers in Hoshiarpur village, New Chandigarh, are still awaiting commercial sites promised by GMADA under the Eco City II scheme since their land acquisition in 2013. While monetary compensation was paid, those who opted for plots only received a letter of intent, hindering their plans for commercial development.
